  "chapter": {
    "number": 24,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Judgment on the Earth"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the LORD lays waste the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and leaves it in ruins.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will twist its surface",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and scatter its inhabitants—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "people and priest alike, servant and master,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "maid and mistress, buyer and seller,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "lender and borrower, creditor and debtor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The earth will be utterly laid waste",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and thoroughly plundered.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "For the LORD has spoken this word."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The earth mourns and withers;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the world languishes and fades;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the exalted of the earth waste away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The earth is defiled by its people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have transgressed the laws;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they have overstepped the decrees",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and broken the everlasting covenant.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore a curse has consumed the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and its inhabitants must bear the guilt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the earth’s dwellers have been burned,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and only a few survive.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The new wine dries up, the vine withers.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "All the merrymakers now groan.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The joyful tambourines have ceased;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the noise of revelers has stopped;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the joyful harp is silent.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They no longer sing and drink wine;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "strong drink is bitter to those who consume it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The city of chaos is shattered;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "every house is closed to entry.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the streets they cry out for wine.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "All joy turns to gloom;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "rejoicing is exiled from the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The city is left in ruins;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "its gate is reduced to rubble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So will it be on the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and among the nations,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like a harvested olive tree,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a gleaning after a grape harvest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They raise their voices, they shout for joy;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the west",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2595
          },
          {
            "text": "they proclaim the majesty of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore glorify the LORD in the east.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Extol the name of the LORD, the God of Israel",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in the islands",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2596
          },
          {
            "text": "of the sea.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From the ends of the earth we hear singing:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Glory to the Righteous One.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "But I said, “I am wasting away! I am wasting away!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Woe is me.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The treacherous betray;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the treacherous deal in treachery.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Terror and pit and snare await you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O dweller of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever flees the sound of panic",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will fall into the pit,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and whoever climbs from the pit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be caught in the snare.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "For the windows of heaven are open,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the foundations of the earth are shaken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The earth is utterly broken apart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the earth is split open,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the earth is shaken violently.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The earth staggers like a drunkard",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sways like a shack.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Earth’s rebellion weighs it down,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and it falls, never to rise again.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day the LORD will punish",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the host of heaven above",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the kings of the earth below.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will be gathered together",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like prisoners in a pit.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will be confined to a dungeon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and punished after many days.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The moon will be confounded",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the sun will be ashamed;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD of Hosts will reign",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and before His elders with great glory.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
